CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper April 9, 1960, pg. A7, reads: "Vying for Crown - One of these lovely contestants may be crowned 'Queen' of the fourth annual May Festival, which will be sponsored by the Mon Valley Sunday School Association at Good Hope Baptist Church, 415 Lincoln Ave., May 27, at 8:15 P. M. Kathleen Casson, representing St. James AME Church, is seated at left; Ruby Brown of Bethel AME, is seated at right. Standing left to right, are: Lois Knox, Good Hope Baptist; Ernestine Smith, Rodman St. Baptist; Jeanette Nesmith, Park Place AME; Gloria Winston, Wesley Center AME Zion, and Maureen Gordon, Second Baptist Church, Homestead. Contestants from Trinity AME, Morning Star Baptist Church, Clairton, are not in the picture. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Contestants for "Queen" of May Festival of Mon Valley Sunday School Association of Good Hope Baptist Church, seated from left: Kathleen Casson, Ruby Brown; standing: Lois Knox, Ernestine Smith, Jeanette Nesmith, Gloria Winston, and Maureen Gordon,
